# Hunt project context

This is a **crypto signal-analytics system**, NOT a trading bot.
No order placement, no account management, no private API keys.

## Stack
- Python 3.14, uv, CCXT (async REST + WS), Polars, aiogram, Pydantic, Structlog, aiohttp
- No pandas, no requests, no dataclasses for domain models

## Architecture
- `market/` — CCXT client, rate limiting, WS/REST transport
- `prizrak/` — Deep engine (pinned majors), NEVER imports scanner
- `scanner/` — Universe pre-pump/detection, NEVER imports prizrak
- `signals/` — Shared Signal model, dedup, lifecycle
- `deliver/` — Telegram formatting (zero business logic)
- `features/` — Polars feature engineering (no architectural choices)
- `domain/` — Pydantic models (no I/O, no CCXT)

## CCXT rules (public only)
**Allowed:** `fetchTicker(s)`, `fetchOHLCV`, `fetchOrderBook`, `fetchTrades`,
`fetchOpenInterest`, `fetchFundingRate`, `fetchMarkets`, `fetchLeverageTiers`,
`watchTicker(s)`, `watchOHLCV`, `watchOrderBook`, `watchTrades`
**Forbidden:** `createOrder`, `cancelOrder`, `editOrder`, `fetchBalance`,
`fetchPositions`, `fetchMyTrades`, `setLeverage`, `setMarginMode`, `withdraw`

## Coding rules
- Polars only, no pandas. Expression API > Python loops. LazyFrame preferred.
- Entirely async (aiohttp). No requests, no blocking calls.
- Structlog for all logging, no stdlib logging.
- Pydantic BaseModel for domain models.
- Every function: full type hints + Google-style docstring.
- Ruff: line-length 100, py314. Ignores E402, E741, F811, F821.
- No eval/exec, no magic numbers, no commented-out code.

